Always process individual ingredients first using tools. Use 'stove' on raw protein/vegetable for 'cooked' items (value 20). Combining two processed ingredients (e.g., cooked protein + cooked vegetable) yields 60. Combining these two with a third processed grain (e.g., cooked protein + cooked vegetable + soaked grain) yields 80. Critically, do NOT combine more than three components, or use tools on already combined items with 3+ components. This will result in 'overcomplicated' or 'overcooked' items with 0 or negative value. Stop at 80 points with three components.
